criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Female patient;

          -  Diagnosed in one of the participating centers with at least one pelvic mass that is
             suspected to be of ovarian origin;

          -  Are to undergo surgery in order to obtain a final histological diagnosis;

          -  18 years of age or older.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnant patients;

          -  Patients aged under 18 years;

          -  Patients in whom the surgery does not take place, or takes place more than 120 days
             after RMI and simple ultrasound-based rules are performed;

          -  Patients with a prior bilateral oophorectomy;

          -  Patients with insufficient or missing data;

          -  Patients who do not give or are incapable of giving an informed consent;

          -  Patients who are not able or willing to travel to the center hospital for additional
             diagnostic procedures.
